1
00:00:00,967 --> 00:00:02,400
<i>Oh, wow! It looks like
Gio's earning money.</i>

2
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:03,800
<i>We're finally getting
our money.</i>

3
00:00:03,933 --> 00:00:04,967
<i> It actually feels weird.</i>

4
00:00:05,100 --> 00:00:06,433
<i> None of them are here.</i>

5
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:08,467
<i>Yes, Lord!
This is the life, Lord.</i>

6
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:10,967
<i>We just want to invite
Mrs. Almazan</i>

7
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:11,933
<i> to the police station.</i>

8
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:13,700
<i> We know about the earring.</i>

9
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,200
<i> I need my lawyer.</i>

10
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:17,533
<i>How did the cops find out
about the earring?</i>

11
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:18,933
<i> Why did you do that?</i>

12
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:22,033
<i>Because I'm tired
of all the lies, Luna!</i>

13
00:00:22,133 --> 00:00:24,033
<i>Let's assume what
you're saying is true.</i>

14
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:25,567
<i> Can't you forgive our mom?</i>

15
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:27,567
<i> Don't tell me</i>

16
00:00:27,733 --> 00:00:31,200
<i>you're thinking your mother
killed your father</i>

17
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,700
<i>so she and my father
could be together.</i>

18
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:33,700
<i> Are you serious?</i>

19
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:36,433
<i>I don't know, Kiko!
I really don't know!</i>

20
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:39,933
<i>That's why I need your help
to find out the truth!</i>

21
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,967
<i>So, tell me right now.
Yes or no?</i>

22
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:43,467
<i> Can you help me?</i>

23
00:00:44,433 --> 00:00:51,433
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

24
00:00:58,933 --> 00:00:59,967
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

25
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:06,300
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

26
00:01:10,467 --> 00:01:17,467
[FOREBODING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

27
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:42,467
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

28
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:35,200
Okay.

29
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:36,533
Okay, okay.

30
00:02:36,733 --> 00:02:37,867
- What are you doing here?
- Bye.

31
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:39,067
I've got to go.

32
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:42,533
We have work to do.

33
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:45,033
Hotel 88 has a big event
that we're preparing for.

34
00:02:45,133 --> 00:02:47,200
[JUSTIN]
What if the cops show up again?

35
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,867
Or someone else bothers Mom?

36
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,033
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:51,733
[JUSTIN] You said so yourself.

38
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:53,267
We need to protect them.

39
00:02:53,433 --> 00:02:54,600
[LUNA] Justin is right, Leon.

40
00:02:55,667 --> 00:02:57,967
Hey, you can't put
your lives on hold

41
00:02:58,100 --> 00:02:59,567
just because of
what's happening.

42
00:03:00,267 --> 00:03:01,900
I can protect myself.

43
00:03:02,067 --> 00:03:03,267
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

44
00:03:05,733 --> 00:03:07,133
Roi, is the car ready?

45
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:11,433
Are you going somewhere, Mom?

46
00:03:11,933 --> 00:03:12,733
Yes.

47
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,267
I need to go to our lawyer

48
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:16,400
so we can be ready
for anything.

49
00:03:17,767 --> 00:03:18,800
[FRIDA] I'll be fine.

50
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,300
Anyway, thanks for the flowers.

51
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:25,800
I appreciate it.

52
00:03:27,767 --> 00:03:28,633
Let's go, Roi.

53
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:32,467
I'll be off.

54
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:38,267
- [GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

55
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:41,233
Let's go.

56
00:03:43,133 --> 00:03:43,967
[SIGHS]

57
00:03:44,133 --> 00:03:47,900
[MUSIC BECOMES OMINOUS]

58
00:03:48,467 --> 00:03:50,167
Do you know if the Almazans
are coming today?

59
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,800
I don't know.

60
00:03:52,967 --> 00:03:54,600
But I'm excited to see them,

61
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:56,300
especially Luna.

62
00:03:56,467 --> 00:03:59,467
I want to know why she lied.

63
00:03:59,633 --> 00:04:01,800
We'll find out their answer
when they return.

64
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:03,633
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

65
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:04,767
Wait.

66
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:06,100
Where are you going?

67
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,433
Do you have somewhere to be?

68
00:04:07,533 --> 00:04:09,300
I'm going to send money
to Grandma

69
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:11,967
and meet the sponsor
for the music fest.

70
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:13,333
Alright, go now.

71
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:14,800
I need you here later, okay?

72
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:16,767
Okay.

73
00:04:16,867 --> 00:04:18,967
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

74
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:20,267
Sari.

75
00:04:20,967 --> 00:04:22,267
[MARTIN] Where are you going?

76
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:23,767
I'm just going to
drink some water, sir.

77
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:25,800
Have you gotten
the tourism officer's signature?

78
00:04:25,967 --> 00:04:27,167
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

79
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:28,800
- Uh...
- Where is it?

80
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:31,200
I haven't gotten it yet.

81
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:33,300
It's just one signature, Sari!

82
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:34,533
Now, tell me

83
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,667
how we're going to start
the event without a permit.

84
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:40,667
The tourism officer will
be back tomorrow.

85
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:42,133
I'll get it in time.

86
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:43,500
So, just chill. Relax, sir.

87
00:04:43,667 --> 00:04:45,033
- Do you want a massage?
- Hey.

88
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,000
I don't have time
to joke around with you.

89
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,567
Uh...

90
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,167
You see, sir...

91
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:52,467
I did my best to get
the signature today.

92
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:55,067
Unfortunately, I ended up there
during lunch break.

93
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,833
I tried to wait.

94
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,367
But it turns out

95
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:02,033
the person who was supposed
to sign it already went home.

96
00:05:02,233 --> 00:05:04,567
I bet they were just
waiting for a bribe.

97
00:05:04,733 --> 00:05:05,700
[LIGHTHEARTED MUSIC PLAYING]

98
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,833
Oh, come on!
Seriously? A bribe?

99
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:09,533
[HUFFS]

100
00:05:09,633 --> 00:05:11,433
Maybe they just wanted to rest.

101
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:16,000
Or maybe they just wanted
to lie down and relax.

102
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:16,833
Something like that.

103
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:18,733
They should've delegated it
to someone else

104
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:19,833
instead of just leaving,

105
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:21,900
knowing that they had left
some work undone.

106
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,367
[SIGHS]

107
00:05:23,467 --> 00:05:24,367
You have a point.

108
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:25,767
I always have a point!

109
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:28,567
This is exactly what's
wrong with the system!

110
00:05:28,733 --> 00:05:30,733
Those slowpokes don't have
any sense of urgency!

111
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:32,033
How will we have progress

112
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:35,433
if they can't even accomplish
something this small quickly?

113
00:05:36,767 --> 00:05:37,700
[HUFFS]

114
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:39,567
[CLAPS]

115
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:40,933
What?

116
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:43,133
What do you mean
by "what," sir?

117
00:05:43,267 --> 00:05:44,400
Raphie!

118
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:45,400
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

119
00:05:45,567 --> 00:05:48,767
[LIGHTHEARTED MUSIC CONTINUES]

120
00:05:51,133 --> 00:05:52,267
Raphie!

121
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:53,733
Hey! What are you doing there?

122
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:55,133
- Sir Martin is calling for--
- Shh!

123
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:57,400
That's exactly why I'm hiding.

124
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:59,533
Whenever Sari messes up,

125
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:02,267
he always calls for me,
"Raphie! Raphie! Raphie!"

126
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:05,700
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

127
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,733
Two weeks.

128
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,100
One day.

129
00:06:08,533 --> 00:06:09,633
You're exaggerating!

130
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:10,467
One week.

131
00:06:10,633 --> 00:06:12,167
- Two days.
- Five days.

132
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,733
Let's just go with three days.

133
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:15,600
No more, no less. Final answer.

134
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:17,733
That's my best bet.

135
00:06:18,167 --> 00:06:19,933
Hey, this isn't some game.

136
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,933
[RAPHIE] But kidding aside,

137
00:06:22,033 --> 00:06:24,000
look at Sir Martin.

138
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:24,933
See?

139
00:06:25,100 --> 00:06:26,467
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

140
00:06:26,633 --> 00:06:29,267
He's boiling with anger.

141
00:06:29,967 --> 00:06:31,967
I bet Sari will resign
in three days.

142
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:33,267
- You sure about that?
- Oh!

143
00:06:33,433 --> 00:06:34,500
You startled me!

144
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:36,433
What do you think you're doing?

145
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,767
Just stay with your boss,
or he'll get even angrier.

146
00:06:38,867 --> 00:06:39,600
My goodness!

147
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:41,267
He's really one of a kind!

148
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,633
He's so handsome,
so responsible,

149
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,800
so smart...

150
00:06:44,967 --> 00:06:46,300
He's so perfect!

151
00:06:46,467 --> 00:06:48,467
My god! Is he even human?

152
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,800
Well...

153
00:06:49,967 --> 00:06:51,033
Is she even human?

154
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:52,333
I don't think so.

155
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:54,133
[GIGGLES]

156
00:06:55,167 --> 00:06:58,000
Grandma, I've sent the budget
for this week.

157
00:06:59,000 --> 00:06:59,967
[PANTS]

158
00:07:00,067 --> 00:07:00,933
What for?

159
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:03,433
I already told you
there's still a lot left.

160
00:07:05,233 --> 00:07:07,133
Well, it's better
to have some extra.

161
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:13,433
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

162
00:07:15,033 --> 00:07:18,200
<i>You know, grandson,
even though I miss you...</i>

163
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:22,500
I'm happy because I know
you're enjoying your stay

164
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,867
at your father's hotel.

165
00:07:24,033 --> 00:07:26,667
We're just here
to settle something.

166
00:07:26,767 --> 00:07:28,800
<i> That's basically the same!</i>

167
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:29,867
<i> I know you.</i>

168
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:33,000
<i>I know that you're enjoying
what you're doing.</i>

169
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:33,800
Of course, Grandma.

170
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,700
If the hotel is
in a good state,

171
00:07:35,867 --> 00:07:37,500
I can sell my shares faster.

172
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:39,333
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:40,633
What?

174
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:42,833
You're still going to sell it?

175
00:07:44,067 --> 00:07:45,167
But...

176
00:07:45,267 --> 00:07:46,867
what about your siblings?

177
00:07:49,967 --> 00:07:52,567
I'll only sell it
to a good person...

178
00:07:52,733 --> 00:07:54,333
someone I know
they can get along with.

179
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:55,500
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

180
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,400
Do you expect me
to stay here forever?

181
00:07:57,567 --> 00:07:58,667
No way!

182
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,667
I still want to go back there.

183
00:08:04,867 --> 00:08:05,267
[GIO'S GRANDMOTHER SIGHS]

184
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:09,567
[EDWARD] Dad.

185
00:08:09,933 --> 00:08:10,933
Hey, bud.

186
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,367
So...

187
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,733
Everything's good,
everything's good?

188
00:08:16,733 --> 00:08:19,433
Tell me. How is it working
with the Almazans?

189
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,767
It's alright, Dad.

190
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,433
The event is coming up.

191
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:26,567
Oh, by the way if you want
to come,

192
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,633
you're very much welcome.

193
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:31,900
Me, go to the event?
I don't think so, man.

194
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,433
I have a lot of work
to finish here

195
00:08:34,433 --> 00:08:36,067
and beside I don't fit in
with those things anymore,

196
00:08:36,067 --> 00:08:37,800
you know I'm-- [CLICKS TONGUE]

197
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:39,533
I'm just meant to take it easy.

198
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:41,933
I get it. Understandable.

199
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,767
So, uh, on another note,

200
00:08:45,767 --> 00:08:47,900
bud, you do realize that...

201
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:51,400
We own almost everything
on this island

202
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:53,467
except for Hotel 88.

203
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:57,467
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

204
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,600
Yeah...

205
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:01,633
Is this the reason
why you agreed to--

206
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:03,433
Look. Try to understand it.

207
00:09:03,433 --> 00:09:04,833
First and foremost,

208
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:06,800
your dad's a business man,
you know?

209
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:10,967
Uh... I will do everything
I can in my power

210
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:13,600
to secure our legacy
on this island.

211
00:09:16,667 --> 00:09:19,500
But I thought you'd just
give them a hand, Dad?

212
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,700
Yes.

213
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,000
I said it and I will.

214
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,467
Don't get me wrong,
of course I'll help them.

215
00:09:24,933 --> 00:09:26,133
Okay.

216
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:30,500
But, Dad, they don't plan
on selling Hotel 88.

217
00:09:30,867 --> 00:09:32,600
If it's what
you're thinking about.

218
00:09:33,467 --> 00:09:35,067
The Almazan siblings,

219
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,533
or rather, Jade
and her siblings,

220
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:38,833
they don't have any plan
to do so

221
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,633
whatsoever.

222
00:09:41,567 --> 00:09:43,033
[CHUCKLING] They don't have to.

223
00:09:43,033 --> 00:09:44,833
They don't have to sell it.

224
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:47,467
If you and Jade get together

225
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:49,200
isn't it basically
the same thing?

226
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,867
I told you this
many times already.

227
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:53,933
I have no plans
to be serious with her.

228
00:09:54,467 --> 00:09:55,600
Okay, then.

229
00:09:55,967 --> 00:09:56,833
I'll uh,

230
00:09:56,833 --> 00:09:58,700
I'll just have to find
another way.

231
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,867
[PHONE RINGING]

232
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:03,700
Excuse me, I have to take this.

233
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:04,867
Sure, sure, sure.

234
00:10:05,567 --> 00:10:07,567
[PHONE RINGING CONTINUES]

235
00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:11,733
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

236
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:13,967
Okay, Sir Henri, Thanks.

237
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:15,933
What did he say?

238
00:10:15,933 --> 00:10:17,867
It's circumstantial.

239
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:21,100
Just because Aunt Frida
is the owner of the earring

240
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:23,033
doesn't mean she was there
during the murder.

241
00:10:23,567 --> 00:10:25,700
They said she could have went
on a different day.

242
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:26,900
Seriously?

243
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:28,967
Or...

244
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:31,033
That family
is just really powerful.

245
00:10:31,033 --> 00:10:37,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

246
00:10:37,767 --> 00:10:39,567
The Almazans are here, sir.

247
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:43,667
[GIO SCOFFS] Oh?

248
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:46,200
The powerful family is here.

249
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:48,833
I thought...

250
00:10:49,533 --> 00:10:50,700
You'll all be absent again.

251
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:52,900
Why would we be absent?

252
00:10:54,267 --> 00:10:55,567
I don't know.

253
00:10:56,733 --> 00:10:57,767
Guilt trip?

254
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:00,067
What are you talking about,
Gio?

255
00:11:01,233 --> 00:11:02,933
Why would we feel guilty?

256
00:11:03,933 --> 00:11:05,933
Come on. [SCOFFS]

257
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:07,933
You don't know?

258
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:11,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

259
00:11:11,767 --> 00:11:13,267
Aren't you the liar?

260
00:11:14,267 --> 00:11:17,633
You said that the earring
was yours but it wasn't.

261
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:18,733
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

262
00:11:26,733 --> 00:11:27,800
[SCOFFS]

263
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,067
Oh, okay.

264
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:30,867
It all makes sense now.

265
00:11:31,967 --> 00:11:33,733
Were you the ones
who reported to the police?

266
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:35,733
Yes.

267
00:11:35,733 --> 00:11:37,067
Why? Is it wrong?

268
00:11:38,067 --> 00:11:39,600
Without asking us first?

269
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:41,167
To know about our side
of the story?

270
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,300
Why?

271
00:11:42,667 --> 00:11:44,600
So that you could cook up
another lie?

272
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:48,967
Why did you even lie, Luna?

273
00:11:52,033 --> 00:11:53,567
What are you hiding?

274
00:11:55,667 --> 00:11:57,267
Are you scared the truth
might get exposed?

275
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:59,933
- Hey watch your mouth, jerk!
- Shut your mouth, loser!

276
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:02,967
I lied because I know
it's going to end up like this.

277
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,833
I just don't want things
to get messy.

278
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:09,600
But because of what you did,
we got even more suspicious.

279
00:12:10,133 --> 00:12:12,267
We were just trying
to protect our family.

280
00:12:12,267 --> 00:12:13,500
How about us then?

281
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,167
Huh?

282
00:12:15,633 --> 00:12:17,800
Don't we have the right
to know the truth?

283
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:21,033
Okay.

284
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:22,300
I understand.

285
00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:26,667
But now that you've reported it
to the police,

286
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,633
What?

287
00:12:28,633 --> 00:12:29,833
Found something?

288
00:12:33,867 --> 00:12:35,000
[JUSTIN] See?

289
00:12:35,567 --> 00:12:36,533
[SCOFFS]

290
00:12:36,533 --> 00:12:38,900
No matter how many times
you file a report,

291
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:40,700
you won't find anything.

292
00:12:42,033 --> 00:12:42,867
So from now on,

293
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:44,600
we'll forget
this ever happened.

294
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,800
We're sorry that Luna lied.

295
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:50,567
But I assure you

296
00:12:51,067 --> 00:12:54,733
my mom, or anyone else
in our family, is innocent.

297
00:12:54,733 --> 00:13:01,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

298
00:13:10,233 --> 00:13:12,567
This is okay
for the suppliers.

299
00:13:12,567 --> 00:13:14,533
- Yes, ma'am, copy.
- Thank you.

300
00:13:15,667 --> 00:13:22,567
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

301
00:13:35,233 --> 00:13:38,000
[FOOTSTEPS]

302
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:43,600
What are you doing here?

303
00:13:44,133 --> 00:13:47,067
Are you still insisting we had
something to do with the case?

304
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:52,000
Your brother said to forget it.

305
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:54,767
But it seems like you're
the one who can't forget.

306
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:59,067
Come to think of it,
why are you the angry one?

307
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:01,633
When you're the one
who didn't tell the truth?

308
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:04,900
Wait.

309
00:14:07,167 --> 00:14:09,467
I didn't come here
to start a fight.

310
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:12,467
I have something to say.

311
00:14:12,467 --> 00:14:14,033
Make sure that's worth
my time.

312
00:14:16,767 --> 00:14:19,733
I can't really talk nonsense
with you, can I?

313
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:22,567
But before...

314
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:24,900
Wait.

315
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:32,000
You've really done nothing
but irritate me, huh?

316
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:38,600
I was in town earlier today
to talk to a possible sponsor

317
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,667
for the music festival.

318
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:42,767
And?

319
00:14:43,967 --> 00:14:44,933
And...

320
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,800
They don't want
to talk to me.

321
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:48,767
[LUNA SCOFFS]

322
00:14:48,767 --> 00:14:49,767
What did you expect?

323
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,967
They said,
it's the General Manager

324
00:14:52,967 --> 00:14:54,267
they want to speak with.

325
00:14:56,133 --> 00:14:57,633
That's you, isn't it?

326
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:02,600
Or do you want me
to send Martin instead?

327
00:15:04,233 --> 00:15:06,133
That's not a difficult thing
to do.

328
00:15:06,133 --> 00:15:07,633
In fact, it would be easier.

329
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:11,000
After all, the sponsor may not
like liars.

330
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:13,800
Aren't you going to stop?

331
00:15:15,233 --> 00:15:16,933
Fine, I'll stop.

332
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,833
What, will it be Martin or you?

333
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:26,767
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

334
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:28,967
[KIKO SIGHS]

335
00:15:28,967 --> 00:15:31,233
What will I tell my brothers?

336
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:33,167
[CHESKA SCOFFS]
Look at this guy.

337
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:35,067
You really don't use your head.

338
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:36,667
Bro, what do you mean
what will you tell them?

339
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:37,767
Why will you say anything?

340
00:15:37,767 --> 00:15:39,200
Because Jade wants to know

341
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:42,300
if Papa and Aunt Frida did have
an affair.

342
00:15:43,667 --> 00:15:46,200
What's it to her
if she finds out the answer?

343
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:48,333
If we discover
that Jade is right,

344
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:50,867
there's a possibility
Aunt Frida had something to do

345
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:52,167
with Papa's death.

346
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:54,867
And then?

347
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:57,267
Bro, there's no "then" yet!

348
00:15:57,267 --> 00:15:59,867
I want to know
if I should tell my brothers.

349
00:16:00,567 --> 00:16:01,600
[CHESKA SIGHS]

350
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:02,633
If you tell them...

351
00:16:03,267 --> 00:16:05,733
If they find out about it...

352
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:11,000
They're going to be angry.
They're going to be angry, bro.

353
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:14,900
I know. That's why I'm having
second thoughts as well.

354
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:17,033
Mm! And when they get angry...

355
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:20,100
You're finished.
You're finished!

356
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,900
Anger will control them.

357
00:16:22,900 --> 00:16:25,033
How then will you get
the right answer,

358
00:16:25,033 --> 00:16:27,100
and how will you know
what really happened

359
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:28,933
if you let anger sway
your decisions?

360
00:16:28,933 --> 00:16:30,967
They'll go straight
to the police station.

361
00:16:30,967 --> 00:16:34,133
It'll be a huge drama.
It'll be a huge mess.

362
00:16:34,133 --> 00:16:37,367
And there's more. There's more!
Prepare yourself.

363
00:16:37,367 --> 00:16:39,033
- You ready?
- What is it?

364
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,867
She'll get angry at you.

365
00:16:43,133 --> 00:16:44,100
[CHESKA] See?

366
00:16:45,267 --> 00:16:46,733
Bro...

367
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:50,400
She'll never, ever
trust you again.

368
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,767
That'll hurt!

369
00:16:51,767 --> 00:16:53,833
She'll ignore you...

370
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:56,100
You'll become like a rat
in her eyes.

371
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:57,900
- A rat, really?
- Why?

372
00:16:57,900 --> 00:16:59,600
Are you okay
with being a rat?

373
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:01,767
[KIKO SIGHS, GROANS]

374
00:17:01,767 --> 00:17:03,800
You're just messing
with my brain.

375
00:17:05,167 --> 00:17:07,267
Come on, bro,
just trust me.

376
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:09,433
- Your crush is right, okay?
- She's not my crush.

377
00:17:09,433 --> 00:17:11,033
Oh, stop it.

378
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:13,867
You can't fool me, what do you
mean she's not your crush?

379
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,967
Anyway, Jade is right!

380
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:21,033
There might be a way
for you to know the truth...

381
00:17:21,033 --> 00:17:22,967
...with just
the two of you knowing.

382
00:17:22,967 --> 00:17:26,933
Right? And then once you
piece together everything,

383
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:28,900
you already collected
a lot of evidence...

384
00:17:29,967 --> 00:17:31,933
Then go ahead
and tell your siblings.

385
00:17:32,767 --> 00:17:33,733
Do you get it?

386
00:17:38,133 --> 00:17:39,233
[KIKO SIGHS DEEPLY]

387
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:42,667
You really need me
in your life, bro.

388
00:17:43,867 --> 00:17:44,900
I got you.

389
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:50,333
- Hurry.
- I'll help you.

390
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:51,233
We'll figure this out together.

391
00:17:51,233 --> 00:17:52,900
Just promise me
no one else will know

392
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:54,133
until we find out the truth.

393
00:17:54,133 --> 00:17:58,200
There's no need for promises.
That's what I want too.

394
00:17:58,567 --> 00:18:01,300
We're talking about
my mother here.

395
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:03,433
We're investigating
my father, too.

396
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:05,300
Come on.
Just swear on it.

397
00:18:05,867 --> 00:18:07,000
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

398
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:21,233
- What?
- Look.

399
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:24,033
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

400
00:18:24,067 --> 00:18:25,267
They're here.

401
00:18:25,267 --> 00:18:26,600
- They're here.
- Ow!

402
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,900
Let's go! We have to hide.

403
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,667
Over there! Hurry!

404
00:18:33,533 --> 00:18:40,233
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

405
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:44,167
They're here again.

406
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:54,133
Three days and
two nights, right?

407
00:18:57,233 --> 00:18:59,133
Oh, the boys aren't here, sir.

408
00:18:59,133 --> 00:19:01,600
They went to town.
How can we help you?

409
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:04,133
We just want to ask
about their father, Michael.

410
00:19:04,133 --> 00:19:05,200
What about him?

411
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,667
Maybe Monette and I
can answer your question.

412
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:11,033
Did you notice anything unusual

413
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:13,533
on the day Mr. Michael Fernandez

414
00:19:13,533 --> 00:19:15,867
and Mr. Federico Alamazan
killed each other?

415
00:19:15,867 --> 00:19:18,767
Sir, you've already
asked me that before.

416
00:19:18,767 --> 00:19:21,533
My answer's the same.

417
00:19:21,533 --> 00:19:25,000
Have we mentioned the envelope
Sir Mike was carrying?

418
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:30,233
What envelope?

419
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:37,067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

420
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:57,967
<i> Ah, sir?</i>

421
00:19:57,967 --> 00:20:00,133
<i> Sir, have you seen the...</i>

422
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:06,933
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

423
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:20,600
Yes, I'm sure.

424
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:23,667
I was the one who put
the envelope on his table.

425
00:20:23,667 --> 00:20:26,667
He had the envelope with him
when he left that day.

426
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,800
Do you know where it is now?

427
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:33,200
We didn't see any envelope
at the scene of the crime.

428
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:40,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

429
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,833
- Ah!
- [METAL TRAY CLANGS]

430
00:20:48,833 --> 00:20:49,867
Ow!

431
00:20:49,867 --> 00:20:51,800
[BREATH SHAKES] Ow...

432
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,667
- [FRIDA] Aah...
- Ma'am?

433
00:20:53,667 --> 00:20:54,900
Ah...

434
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,300
- Ow...
- What happened, ma'am?

435
00:20:56,300 --> 00:20:58,733
I burned my fingers
on the hot tray.

436
00:20:58,733 --> 00:21:00,867
I forgot to wear gloves.

437
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:03,733
[OBJECTS CLATTERING]

438
00:21:03,733 --> 00:21:05,200
[FRIDA] There.

439
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,633
Right there.

440
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:13,200
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

441
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:17,900
[HISSES IN PAIN,
BREATHES DEEPLY]

442
00:21:19,033 --> 00:21:20,233
Are you all right, ma'am?

443
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:22,300
Yeah, I'm good. Thank you.

444
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:31,067
[SUCKS TEETH,
BREATHES DEEPLY]

445
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:36,933
[FRIDA BREATHES DEEPLY]

446
00:21:36,933 --> 00:21:41,867
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

447
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:50,167
[EDWARD] Jade.

448
00:21:52,067 --> 00:21:55,100
So this is where you are.
I've been looking for you.

449
00:21:58,967 --> 00:22:00,567
[EDWARD]
Where are you going?

450
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,567
We were supposed to meet,
remember?

451
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:07,233
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

452
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:08,867
Oh, right.

453
00:22:10,567 --> 00:22:14,100
Sorry, is it okay if
we bring Kiko along?

454
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:17,900
Why?

455
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,633
- Why not?
- [EDWARD SCOFFS]

456
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:22,067
Are you in charge of marketing?

457
00:22:22,167 --> 00:22:25,233
I heard you're on
housekeeping duties.

458
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:27,400
- Food and beverage.
- Food and beverage?

459
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:29,100
That's perfect.

460
00:22:32,933 --> 00:22:34,100
Go to this address.

461
00:22:39,967 --> 00:22:41,733
I know them personally.

462
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:44,867
They can supply the best wine
for the music fest.

463
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:46,733
I already called them.

464
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:49,867
All you have to do
is meet with them for formality.

465
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:54,433
[INHALES DEEPLY]

466
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:56,433
Okay. Thank you.

467
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:57,767
No problem.

468
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:06,833
The boat's here, Jade.

469
00:23:08,133 --> 00:23:09,267
Let's go?

470
00:23:13,433 --> 00:23:14,767
Huh?

471
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:17,400
I thought we're having
a meeting.

472
00:23:19,667 --> 00:23:22,000
Can't we do it on a boat?

473
00:23:28,333 --> 00:23:29,800
Let's go?

474
00:23:35,067 --> 00:23:36,100
Come on.

475
00:23:41,633 --> 00:23:42,933
Let's go.

476
00:23:48,167 --> 00:23:50,500
<i> Hey! Edward! Edward!</i>

477
00:23:50,667 --> 00:23:53,600
<i>What are you doing? We were
supposed to have a meeting!</i>

478
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,633
<i>We're in the sea!
There are no rules!</i>

479
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:57,500
<i> Join me! Let's talk here!</i>

480
00:23:57,600 --> 00:23:59,667
<i> Cancel the island hopping!</i>

481
00:23:59,767 --> 00:24:02,733
<i>Ma'am is here,
and she's excited!</i>

482
00:24:02,867 --> 00:24:04,833
Raphie, find me a new assistant.

483
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:07,233
<i>Someone who isn't loud
and knows what they're doing.</i>

484
00:24:07,367 --> 00:24:09,667
<i>What happened to Sari?
Has she resigned already?</i>

485
00:24:09,733 --> 00:24:11,233
It doesn't matter <i> how important
</i> that envelope is

486
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:12,467
<i> if we can't even find it.</i>

487
00:24:12,533 --> 00:24:13,867
<i>If it disappeared
from the crime scene,</i>

488
00:24:13,933 --> 00:24:16,733
<i>someone else
could've been there.</i>

